  "prompt": "What are the top 10 inspirational movies of the 21st century?",
  "response": "Here\u2019s a list of ten highly inspirational movies from the 21st century, celebrated for their uplifting stories, powerful messages, and motivational themes:\n\n1. **The Pursuit of Happyness (2006)**  \n   - Starring Will Smith, this true story of Chris Gardner\u2019s journey from homelessness to success is a testament to perseverance and determination.\n\n2. **The Secret Life of Walter Mitty (2013)**  \n   - Ben Stiller\u2019s portrayal of a daydreamer who embarks on a life-changing adventure encourages viewers to step out of their comfort zones and embrace life.\n\n3. **Hidden Figures (2016)**  \n   - This true story about three African-American women mathematicians at NASA highlights resilience, intelligence, and breaking barriers in the face of adversity.\n\n4. **The Blind Side (2009)**  \n   - Based on a true story, this film follows Michael Oher, a homeless teen who becomes an NFL star with the support of a loving family.\n\n5. **A Beautiful Mind (2001)**  \n   - The story of mathematician John Nash\u2019s struggle with schizophrenia and his eventual triumph is a powerful tale of hope and the human spirit.\n\n6. **The Theory of Everything (2014)**  \n   - This biographical film about Stephen Hawking\u2019s life showcases his incredible achievements despite his physical challenges, inspiring resilience and passion.\n\n7. **Rocky Balboa (2006)**  \n   - The sixth installment in the Rocky series reminds us that it\u2019s never too late to pursue your dreams and fight for what you believe in.\n\n8. **Slumdog Millionaire (2008)**  \n   - A story of determination and hope, this film follows a young man from the slums of Mumbai who overcomes immense odds to change his life.\n\n9. **Lion (2016)**  \n   - Based on a true story, this emotional journey of a man searching for his lost family is a testament to the power of love and perseverance.\n\n10. **The Help (2011)**  \n    - This film about African-American maids in the 1960s who courageously share their stories inspires hope, change, and the fight for justice.\n\nThese films resonate with audiences for their messages of hope, resilience, and the power of the human spirit to overcome challenges.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
